Cluniac Reforms<br>
<br>
- mandatory clerical celibacy and the elimination of concubinage (at this point celibacy was only mandatory for monks, not priests)<br>
<br>
- eliminate simony<br>
<br>
- eliminate nepotism<br>
<br>
- enforce rigid obedience to the abbot or bishop<br>
<br>
- end lay investiture<br>
<br>
- enforce the vow of poverty – this one was never implemented on a large scale<br>
